@maragato2000 we try to use OS safe functions in Python everywhere in the codebase to deal with paths, so directory dividers shouldn't be an issue.
Looking at the code, it looks to me there should be no issue:
https://github.com/ludwig-ai/ludwig/blob/a8165d07a07f41ddee6b1051e37479369c1e40e7/ludwig/data/postprocessing.py#L59

In order to help you out and try to debug then, it would be great if you could provide a small script that can replicate the issue. You can use `synthesyze_dataset` for creting a small dataset programmatically within your script.

@brightsparc FYI as I believe you debugged a similar windows issue in the past.
